<div id="subtree-container" class="subtree-container"><div class="aea2d7dde423afa7ad9351a0886150a8-scss b51b00c1669ad99a1c607cd1e77c2824-scss" style="inset: 531px 269px 0px 0px; justify-content: flex-end;"><div class="afeebf1df237d4103108ba40799802d6-scss"><div class="c13443431e58facf06f9d12490b92a82-scss" style="width: 90vw; max-width: 8.5in;"><div class="_0df5ec6b9902d7d22ccfa3ebb4f35211-scss">Production of Information</div><div class="e5e059a27f4c194020f0d961a3cb5989-scss" dir="auto"><div class="fr-view"><p>The following information should be considered to <strong>support the work activities and contribute to the deliverables</strong>:</p>
<ol>
<li>Project information and design information needed to enable construction</li>
<li>Alignment of the design with the needs of the operator, operations team or facility manager, as appropriate, and end-users in terms of the basis of the design, space, access, adaptability and operational cost, as a minimum</li>
<li>Availability of a procedure or protocol for controlling the distribution of documents, information and data</li>
<li>Requirements to obtain firm price quotations as a precursor to procuring the building services engineering systems and other long-lead items</li>
<li>Updated lead times for building services engineering systems and other major components and systems</li>
<li>Source of specialist maintenance service provision (e.g. lifts/elevators and other specialist building services engineering systems)</li>
<li>Definition and extent of operation and maintenance information&nbsp;</li>
<li>Method statements for work where existing building services engineering systems and public utilities are to interface with the new or refurbished asset/facility</li>
</ol></div></div></div></div></div></div>